  "prompt": "Has the fear of a non wanted pregnancy, as no anticonceptive method is 100% fireproof, ever hindered your desire to have sexual intercourse?",
  "response": "Yes, for some individuals, the fear of an unwanted pregnancy can be a significant concern that impacts their decision to engage in sexual activity. While many contraceptive methods are highly effective, none are completely foolproof. Concerns about the potential consequences of pregnancy, along with other factors such as personal values, health, and relationship dynamics, can indeed affect a person's desire for sexual intimacy. It's important for individuals to communicate openly with their partners and seek information about contraception options to help make informed decisions that align with their personal circumstances and comfort levels.",
